.TH HYPRPM 1 "2025-12-17" "hyprland 0.53.3" "Hyprland Ecosystem"
.SH NAME
hyprpm \- Hyprland plugin manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hyprpm
.I command
.RI [ args ]
.RI [ flags ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hyprpm
is Hyprland's built\-in plugin manager.
It manages installation, enabling, disabling, updating, and removal of
Hyprland plugins from git repositories.
.PP
Plugin repositories must contain a
.I hyprpm.toml
manifest file at the repository root.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BI add " url " \fR[ "git rev" \fR]
Install a plugin repository from a git URL.
An optional git revision can be specified to lock to a specific version.
.TP
.BI remove " url" | name | author/name
Remove an installed plugin repository.
.TP
.BI enable " name" | author/name
Enable a plugin.
.TP
.BI disable " name" | author/name
Disable a plugin.
.TP
.B update
Check for and apply updates to all installed plugins.
.TP
.B reload
Reload hyprpm state and ensure all enabled plugins are loaded.
.TP
.B list
List all installed plugins and their status.
.TP
.B purge\-cache
Remove the entire hyprpm cache, including built plugins, settings, and
headers.
.SH FLAGS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose logging.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Force the operation, ignoring safety checks.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-notify
Send a Hyprland notification on successful plugin load.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-no\-shallow
Disable shallow cloning of Hyprland sources.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-nix
Disable nix develop for build commands.
.TP
.BI \-\-hl\-url " url"
Pass a custom Hyprland source URL.
.SH PREREQUISITES
The following tools are required:
.BR cpio (1),
.BR cmake (1),
.BR git (1),
.BR meson (1),
and a C++ compiler.
On Fedora, development packages (\-devel) may also be needed.
.SH EXAMPLES
Install and enable a plugin:
.PP
.RS
.nf
hyprpm add https://github.com/example/hyprland\-plugin
hyprpm enable plugin\-name
.fi
.RE
.PP
To load plugins at startup, add to
.IR hyprland.conf :
.PP
.RS
.B exec\-once = hyprpm reload
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR Hyprland (1),
.BR hyprctl (1)
